'Seriously Single' is currently being screened at one of the biggest film festivals in America. JOHANNESBURG - Love may be in the air this month,Â but not for two singletons in a new local movie. Seriously Single is currently being screened at one of the biggest film festivals in America. The comedy looks at the dating lives of two best friends. One is a hopeless romantic and the other suffers from commitment phobia. The comedy is currently showing at the Pan African Film and Arts Festival in Los Angeles, California. It was founded by legendary actor Danny Glover and attended by celebs such as Oprah.